title: Author
description: My book Hitting the Innovation Jackpot: Practical Essays on Innovation is available through Amazon. I think that you will find it an easy read and have lots of useful insights whether or not you are a college graduate at your first job, a part-time youth basketball coach, or the CEO of a large company. http://www.amazon.com/Hitting-Innovation-Jackpot-Practical-Essays/dp/1462070108/ref=sr_1_5?ie=UTF8&qid=1323611264&sr=8-5 Don't let the success of your company be left to chance. Hitting the Innovation Jackpot takes the mystery and risk out of realizing true value from innovation initiatives that involve all strata of the enterprise: individuals, teams, and the organization. This book will demystify the blur of innovation techniques and terminology that we are all inundated with in the popular press every day. In reality anything has the potential to be an innovation. Some technique or process used routinely in one domain may serve to catalyze a revolution in another domain. So even the simplest insight or approach can become an innovation highlight when used in a different world from which it is normally applied. Hitting the Innovation Jackpot will help you to identify when, where, and how to make this transfer between different domains. By presenting the material in easy-to-digest, practical essays, clarity is brought to the perplexing world of innovation. Essays cover topics ranging from "high tech" methodologies to "high touch" rules and their use across domains ranging from defense industry companies and space operations to high school football and the music industry. Hitting the Innovation Jackpot is the last innovation book you will ever need as it provides both the basics of innovation and how to weave them together into a powerful, executable innovation strategy for your needs, no matter what your challenge.

title: Office Manager
description: Veterans For Peace is a global organization of Military Veterans and allies whose collective efforts are to build a culture of peace by using our experiences and lifting our voices. We inform the public of the true causes of war and the enormous costs of wars, with an obligation to heal the wounds of wars. Our network is comprised of over 140 chapters worldwide whose work includes: educating the public, advocating for a dismantling of the war economy, providing services that assist veterans and victims of war, and most significantly, working to end all wars. We, having dutifully served our nation, do hereby affirm our greater responsibility to serve the cause of world peace. To this end we will work, with others To increase public awareness of the costs of war To restrain our government from intervening, overtly and covertly, in the internal affairs of other nations To end the arms race and to reduce and eventually eliminate nuclear weapons To seek justice for veterans and victims of war To abolish war as an instrument of national policy. To achieve these goals, members of Veterans For Peace pledge to use non-violent means and to maintain an organization that is both democratic and open with the understanding that all members are trusted to act in the best interests of the group for the larger purpose of world peace.
